Homework 3¶

Jan Dziuba

Dataset¶

I chose the MagicTelescope dataset.
Dataset is used for classification of high energy gamma particles in a ground-based atmospheric Cherenkov gamma telescope using the imaging technique.
For more detailed description check
https://www.openml.org/search?type=data&sort=runs&id=1120&status=active

Dataset contains 10 features and 19020 samples.
Classes are imbalanced with 1.8438995215311005 ratio.

3.¶

Compare LIME for various observations in the dataset. How stable are these explanations?

Chosen model was logistic regression.
We can see that importances for different seeds differ.
The most important variable is fLength.
Other variables are of similar importance and their importance varies across the seeds.
fM3Trans variable sometimes has positive and sometimes negative contribution.

For different samples situation is even more unclear.
fLength and fAlpha jump from big positive contribution to big negative contribution.

5.¶

Compare LIME between at least two different models. Are there any systematic differences across many observations?

Differences between random forest and linear regression big and so are differences betweeen different samples.
Depending on the sample models either agree or disagree on importance of different variables.

In [91]:
def evaluate_model(model, X_test, Y_test):
    pred = model.predict(X_test)
    pred_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

    accuracy = accuracy_score(Y_test, pred)
    precision = precision_score(Y_test, pred)
    recall = recall_score(Y_test, pred)
    auc = roc_auc_score(Y_test, pred_proba)
    f1 = f1_score(Y_test, pred)

    print('Accuracy: {}'.format(accuracy))
    print('Precision: {}'.format(precision))
    print('Recall: {}'.format(recall))
    print('AUC: {}'.format(auc))
    print('F1: {}'.format(f1))
